projects.name: Briar
projects.description: A peer-to-peer encrypted messenger designed for activists, journalists, and anyone needing censorship-resistant communication. Can sync messages directly via Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, or Tor - functioning even during internet shutdowns.
privacy_techniques: Built-in onion routing for online anonymity

projects.name: Cake Wallet
projects.description: Open-source, non-custodial, privacy-focused multi-currency cryptocurrency wallet supporting Monero, Bitcoin, Ethereum, Litecoin, and other cryptocurrencies. Features built-in exchange, native Tor integration, Bitcoin privacy tools (Silent Payments, Payjoin), and best-in-class Monero support.

projects.name: Circom
projects.description: zkSnark circuit compiler - A domain-specific language for defining arithmetic circuits that can be used to generate zero-knowledge proofs

projects.name: Concordium
projects.description: A privacy-focused, public, and permissionless Layer-1 blockchain with protocol-level identity verification, zero-knowledge proofs, and built-in compliance features. First blockchain with built-in identity verification at the protocol level.

team.name: Lars Seier Christensen
team.role: Founder and Chairman of Concordium Foundation Board

projects.name: Findora
projects.description: Findora is a Layer-1 blockchain that accelerates mainstream adoption through powerful zero-knowledge solutions and SDKs. It is a decentralized, privacy-preserving smart contract platform featuring programmable privacy, secured by a decentralized network of global validators running the Tendermint consensus mechanism.

projects.name: Firo
projects.description: Privacy-focused cryptocurrency that utilizes the Lelantus Spark protocol which supports high anonymity sets without requiring trusted setup and relying on standard cryptographic assumptions

projects.name: Fluidkey
projects.description: Privacy-preserving wallet using stealth addresses to allow users to receive and manage funds onchain without publicly linking them to their identity. Implements ERC-5564 standard for stealth addresses with integration to ENS.

projects.name: GnuPG
projects.description: A free implementation of the OpenPGP standard (RFC 4880) for encrypting and signing data. Created by Werner Koch in 1999, it serves as the open-source replacement for proprietary PGP. Used by Edward Snowden to evade NSA monitoring.

projects.name: HOPR
projects.description: HOPR provides essential and compliant network-level metadata privacy for everyone. HOPR is an open incentivized mixnet which enables privacy-preserving point-to-point data exchange. HOPR is similar to Tor but actually private, decentralized and economically sustainable.

projects.name: I2P
projects.description: A fully decentralized anonymous overlay network that uses 'garlic routing' (bundling multiple messages) and unidirectional tunnels to provide stronger traffic analysis resistance than traditional onion routing.
privacy_techniques: Bundles multiple messages ('cloves') vs single-message onion routing
No central directory servers like Tor

projects.name: iden3
projects.description: Blockchain-based identity management solution including privacy by design with zkSNARKs. Self-sovereign identity protocol for decentralised and trust-minimised environments.

projects.name: Iron Fish
projects.description: A novel cryptocurrency focused on privacy and accessibility. Iron Fish encrypts every transaction, shielding your sensitive asset information from public view. With read-only view keys, you remain compliant and in control.

projects.name: Monero
projects.description: Monero: the secure, private, untraceable cryptocurrency. Private, decentralized cryptocurrency that keeps your finances confidential and secure.
privacy_techniques: Untraceable transactions with ring signatures, stealth addresses, and confidential transactions

projects.name: Oasis Network
projects.description: Oasis: Smart Privacy for Web3 & AI. Build a better Web3 on the only confidential EVM in production. Scalable & Secure. Interoperable by design.

projects.name: Orchid
projects.description: The Orchid Protocol organizes bandwidth sellers into a structured peer-to-peer (P2P) network termed the Orchid Market. A decentralized marketplace for AI, storage, and bandwidth that enables customers to connect to the Orchid Market and pay bandwidth sellers in order to form a proxy chain to a specific resource on the Internet.

projects.name: Oxen
projects.description: Oxen is a private cryptocurrency based on Monero that offers an incentivised full node layer (Service Nodes), an anonymous onion routing network (Lokinet), and a private messenger (Session). The project has transitioned to using SENT token on Arbitrum L2 for staking and rewards while maintaining the Oxen blockchain as a state chain.

projects.name: RAILGUN
projects.description: RAILGUN is a decentralized smart contract system enabling zero-knowledge privacy for on-chain decentralized applications. It uses zk-SNARKs to provide private transactions, shielded balances, and anonymous DeFi interactions directly on Ethereum and other EVM-compatible chains without bridges or separate chains.

projects.name: Semaphore
projects.description: A zero-knowledge protocol for anonymous interactions

projects.name: Tails
projects.description: A portable operating system that protects against surveillance and censorship. Runs from a USB stick, leaves no trace on the host computer, and routes all internet traffic through Tor. Used by Edward Snowden during the NSA revelations.
privacy_techniques: Runs entirely in RAM, never writes to hard drive
Overwrites RAM on shutdown (cold boot attack protection)
Each boot starts from clean state
All internet traffic routed through Tor

projects.name: Tor Project
projects.description: A 501(c)(3) nonprofit that maintains the Tor anonymity network and associated software. Tor enables anonymous communication by routing traffic through a worldwide volunteer network of relays using onion routing.
privacy_techniques: Multi-layer encryption where each relay peels one layer
Every ~10 minutes for traffic analysis resistance

projects.name: Tornado Cash
projects.description: Fully decentralized, non-custodial cryptocurrency mixer protocol that runs on Ethereum Virtual Machine-compatible networks, enabling private transactions using zero-knowledge proof technology. Tornado Cash was sanctioned by OFAC in August 2022 but had sanctions lifted in March 2025 following a Fifth Circuit court ruling.

projects.name: Wasabi Wallet
projects.description: Open-source, non-custodial, privacy preserving Bitcoin wallet for Windows, Linux, and Mac.

projects.name: Webb Protocol
projects.description: Zero-knowledge privacy protocol for building private, decentralized applications with cross-chain capabilities

projects.name: Xx Network
projects.description: Quantum Resistant Decentralized Mixnet with Blockchain

projects.name: YubiKey
projects.description: Hardware security key manufactured by Yubico that provides strong two-factor, multi-factor, and passwordless authentication. Co-authored the FIDO U2F standard with Google.
privacy_techniques: RSA up to 4096 bits, ECC up to 384 bits

projects.name: Zano
projects.description: Zano is an open-source cryptocurrency and ecosystem with enterprise-grade privacy, security, and scalability

projects.name: Zcash
projects.description: The first cryptocurrency to develop zero-knowledge encryption for private peer-to-peer payments

team.name: Zooko Wilcox-O'Hearn
team.role: Founder and former CEO of Electric Coin Company

team.name: J.W. Verret
team.role: Associate Professor at Antonin Scalia Law School

team.name: Peter Van Valkenburgh
team.role: Director of Research at Coin Center

projects.name: zk.money
projects.description: zk.money was a privacy-focused zkRollup wallet built on Aztec Connect protocol, enabling private transactions and DeFi interactions on Ethereum Layer 2 with zero-knowledge proofs. The service has been SUNSET as of March 31, 2024.
